## Document Status Lifecycle

### Complete Status Definitions

| Status | Meaning | When to Use | Typical Duration |
|--------|---------|-------------|------------------|
| **Planning** | Document concept is being scoped and planned | Initial idea phase, gathering requirements | Days to weeks |
| **In Roadmap** | Document is planned for future creation | Scheduled but not started | Weeks to months |
| **Draft** | Document is being actively written | Content incomplete, work in progress | Days to weeks |
| **In Review** | Document complete, awaiting review/approval | Ready for feedback, pending approval | Days |
| **Active** | Current, maintained, and in use | Primary documentation for topic | Months to years |
| **In Progress** | Active document being implemented | Document contents being built into application | Weeks to months |
| **Deprecated** | Still valid but use alternative | Newer approach exists, grace period | 30-90 days |
| **Superseded** | Replaced by newer version | New document completely replaces this one | 30-90 days |
| **Archived** | Historical reference only | No longer relevant, kept for history | Permanent |

### Detailed Status Descriptions

#### Planning
**Definition:** The document concept is being planned. Scope, audience, and content outline are being determined.

**Use When:**
- Initial concept phase for a new document
- Gathering requirements for what the document should cover
- Deciding if a document is needed

**Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** Planning
- **Planned By:** [Name/Team]
- **Target Start Date:** [Date]
```

#### In Roadmap
**Definition:** The document is officially scheduled for creation but work has not yet begun.

**Use When:**
- Document approved for creation
- Scheduled in project roadmap
- Waiting for other work to complete first

**Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** In Roadmap
- **Scheduled For:** Q1 2026
- **Blocked By:** [Optional - what needs to complete first]
```

#### Draft
**Definition:** The document is being actively written. Content may be incomplete or subject to change.

**Use When:**
- Actively writing content
- Document structure is defined but content is partial
- Not ready for use

**Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** Draft
- **Draft Started:** [Date]
- **Target Completion:** [Date]
```

#### In Review
**Definition:** The document is complete and awaiting review or approval before becoming active.

**Use When:**
- Writing is complete
- Pending technical review
- Pending stakeholder approval

**Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** In Review
- **Review Requested:** [Date]
- **Reviewer:** [Name/Team]
```

#### Active
**Definition:** The document is current, maintained, and the authoritative source for its topic.

**Use When:**
- Document is complete and approved
- Being actively maintained
- Should be used as reference

**Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** Active
- **Approved Date:** [Date]
- **Owner:** [Name/Team]
```

#### In Progress
**Definition:** The document describes something being actively implemented in the application. The contents of this document are being built.

**Use When:**
- Feature spec being implemented
- Architecture decision being executed
- Roadmap item in development

**Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** In Progress
- **Implementation Started:** [Date]
- **Target Completion:** [Date]
- **Related PR/Issue:** [Link]
```

**Note:** This is distinct from "Draft" - "In Progress" means the document is complete but what it DESCRIBES is being built.

#### Deprecated
**Definition:** The document is still accurate but a better alternative exists. Users should migrate to the alternative.

**Use When:**
- New approach supersedes old approach
- Old method still works but isn't recommended
- Grace period before archiving

**Required Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** Deprecated
- **Deprecated Date:** [Date]
- **Deprecated Reason:** [Why deprecated]
- **Alternative:** [Link to replacement document or approach]
- **Archive Date:** [Planned archive date, typically 30-90 days]
```

**Required Notice at Top of Document:**
```markdown
> ⚠️ **DEPRECATED:** This document is deprecated as of [Date].
> **Reason:** [Brief reason]
> **Use Instead:** [Link to alternative document]
> **Archive Date:** This document will be archived on [Date].
```

#### Superseded
**Definition:** This document has been replaced by a newer version. The new version is the authoritative source.

**Use When:**
- New version of document created (v1 → v2)
- Document was split into multiple documents
- Document was merged with another

**Required Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** Superseded
- **Superseded Date:** [Date]
- **Superseded By:** [Link to new document]
- **Superseded Reason:** [Why replaced - version update, split, merge]
- **Archive Date:** [Planned archive date]
```

**Required Notice at Top of Document:**
```markdown
> ⚠️ **SUPERSEDED:** This document was superseded on [Date].
> **Replaced By:** [Link to new document]
> **Reason:** [Version update / Split into multiple docs / Merged with X]
> **Archive Date:** This document will be archived on [Date].
```

#### Archived
**Definition:** Historical reference only. Document is no longer maintained or relevant for current work.

**Use When:**
- Grace period after deprecation/supersession ended
- Document no longer applicable
- Kept only for historical reference

**Required Metadata:**
```markdown
- **Status:** Archived
- **Archived Date:** [Date]
- **Archived From:** [Previous status - Deprecated/Superseded]
- **Archived Reason:** [Why archived]
- **Historical Context:** [Brief note on what this was for]
```

**File Location:** Move to `docs/archive/` with `_archived_YYYY-MM-DD` suffix.

